.TH ASSHO 1 "2026-05-16" "assho 0.1.19" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
assho \- Another SSH Organizer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B assho
.RB [ \-\-version ]
.RB [ \-\-help ]
.br
.B assho
.I command
.RI [ argument ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B assho
is a terminal user interface (TUI) for managing and connecting to SSH hosts.
It stores host profiles\(emincluding credentials, port forwarding rules, and
jump hosts\(emin a single config file and lets you connect with a single
keystroke.
Running
.B assho
with no arguments launches the interactive TUI.
Non-interactive subcommands let you connect, test, list, and export hosts
from scripts or shell aliases.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B connect \fIalias\fR
Connect directly to the host or container identified by
.IR alias ,
bypassing the TUI.
Accepts container aliases; SSH tunnels through the parent host and runs
.BR "docker exec" .
.TP
.B test \fIalias\fR
Test SSH connectivity for
.IR alias .
Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.
Works with both host and container aliases.
.TP
.B list
Print all configured hosts as a formatted table.
.TP
.B export
Print all hosts as
.BR ssh_config (5)
stanzas suitable for appending to
.IR ~/.ssh/config ,
so other tools (VS Code Remote, rsync, scp) can see them.
Containers are omitted.
.TP
.B completion \fIshell\fR
Print a shell completion script for
.IR shell .
Supported values:
.BR bash ,
.BR zsh ,
.BR fish .
See
.B SHELL COMPLETIONS
below.
.TP
.B help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version\fR, \fB\-v
Print the version string and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH TUI KEYBINDINGS
.SS Dashboard
.TS
l l.
enter	Connect to selected host
n	New host
e	Edit selected host
c	Duplicate selected host
d \fI(twice)\fR	Delete host or group
p	Pin / unpin host
space / \(->	Expand host (scan Docker containers)
\(<-	Collapse host or group
Ctrl+D	Force re-scan Docker containers
/	Filter / search
h	Recent connection history
i	Import from ~/.ssh/config
K	Open staged fleet key rotation
g	Create group
r	Rename selected group
Shift+\(ua / \(da	Reorder hosts or groups
a	About
?	Keybinding reference
q	Quit
.TE
.SS Add / Edit Form
.TS
l l.
Tab / \(da	Next field
Shift+Tab / \(ua	Previous field
Enter	Advance from text fields or activate the focused control
Ctrl+S	Save from anywhere in the form
Space / Enter	Toggle agent forwarding when focused
\(<- / \(->	Cycle group selection
Ctrl+T	Test connection
Ctrl+K	Install public-key access for the host being edited
?	Keybinding reference
Esc	Cancel
.TE
.PP
Terminals at least 100 columns by 28 rows open the form in a centered modal
over the dimmed dashboard, with a two-column workspace and contextual rail.
Medium and compact terminals use an inset or full-screen scrolling workspace.
The focused control remains visible as the form scrolls.
Terminals smaller than 36 columns by 12 rows show a resize notice.
.SS Key Rotation
Press \fBK\fR on the dashboard to select saved hosts and perform a staged,
sequential key rotation. The replacement public key is installed and verified
before the local IdentityFile is changed or the old remote key is removed.
Before removal, Assho backs up the standard ~/.ssh/authorized_keys file and
performs a final replacement-key verification afterward. Failures are isolated
to the affected host.
.PP
Incomplete runs can be resumed from journals in
~/.config/assho/rotation-runs/. The directory is mode 0700 and journal files
are mode 0600. Journals do not contain passwords or private-key contents.
Assho manages only the standard ~/.ssh/authorized_keys path; alternate
AuthorizedKeysFile or AuthorizedKeysCommand configurations require manual
cleanup. The workflow requires ssh-copy-id and ssh-keygen. When an SSH agent is
active, ssh-add is used once; without an agent, the selected identity is used
directly and must pass strict verification before destructive steps. sshpass is
optional.
.SS Server Host-Key Trust
Before TUI SSH actions, Assho checks the server against the standard user and
system known-hosts files. Unknown servers pause the action and open a reviewed
enrollment flow. OpenSSH displays the SHA256 fingerprint and writes an approved
entry to ~/.ssh/known_hosts. Compare the fingerprint with the server console or
another trusted source. Changed and revoked server keys are never replaced
automatically.
.SS History
.TS
l l.
Enter	Connect
e	Edit host
h / Esc / q	Back to dashboard
.TE
.SH FORM FIELDS
.TP
.B Alias
Friendly name shown in the host list.
Used as the argument to
.B connect
and
.BR test .
.TP
.B Hostname
IP address or domain name of the server.
.TP
.B User
SSH username (e.g.\&
.IR root ,
.IR ubuntu ,
.IR deploy ).
.TP
.B Port
SSH port.
Defaults to 22.
.TP
.B Key File
Path to an SSH private key file (e.g.\&
.IR ~/.ssh/id_rsa ).
Use the
.B Browse
button to browse.
.TP
.B Password
SSH password.
Stored in the OS keychain (macOS Keychain or Linux
.BR secret-tool (1)),
never written to the config file.
.TP
.B Fwd.\& Agent
SSH agent forwarding.
Toggle this control with Space or Enter to pass
.B \-A
to ssh, allowing the remote host to use your local keys.
.TP
.B ProxyJump
A bastion or jump host used to reach this server.
Passed to SSH's
.B \-J
flag.
Format:
.RI [ user@ ] host [: port ]
.TP
.B LocalFwd
A local port forwarding rule.
Passed to SSH's
.B \-L
flag.
Format:
.I local_port\fR:\fIremote_host\fR:\fIremote_port
(e.g.\&
.IR 5432:localhost:5432 ).
.TP
.B Group
Assign the host to a collapsible group.
Use \(la\(ra in the form to cycle through existing groups.
.TP
.B Notes
Free-text note shown beneath the alias in the host list.
.SH SHELL COMPLETIONS
Enable tab-completion for
.B connect
and
.BR test :
.PP
.B bash
\(em add to
.IR ~/.bashrc :
.PP
.RS
.EX
eval "$(assho completion bash)"
.EE
.RE
.PP
.B zsh
\(em add to
.IR ~/.zshrc :
.PP
.RS
.EX
eval "$(assho completion zsh)"
.EE
.RE
.PP
.B fish
\(em run once:
.PP
.RS
.EX
assho completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/assho.fish
.EE
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ASSHO_STORE_PASSWORD
Set to
.B 0
or
.B false
to disable password persistence to the OS keychain.
.TP
.B ASSHO_INSECURE_TEST
Development only. Set to
.B 1
to bypass host key verification during connection tests
.RB ( assho\ test ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/assho/hosts.json
Host profiles, groups, and connection history.
Written with mode 0600.
.TP
.I ~/.ssh/config
Read by
.B assho import
(key
.BR i ).
Written to by
.BR "assho export" .
.SH EXAMPLES
Connect to a host directly:
.PP
.RS
.EX
assho connect prod-web
.EE
.RE
.PP
Test connectivity and use the exit code in a script:
.PP
.RS
.EX
assho test db && pg_dump ...
.EE
.RE
.PP
Export to SSH config so VS Code Remote can see your hosts:
.PP
.RS
.EX
assho export >> ~/.ssh/config
.EE
.RE
.PP
Connect directly to a Docker container on a remote host:
.PP
.RS
.EX
assho connect radarr
.EE
.RE
